68.name: A Northern slope
desc: "   The slope is steep on the north side of the burrow but its soft
green grass is inviting you to a cool spot at its foot. The air is
filled with the sounds of dancing crickets all about you. The view
is breathtaking due to the myriad clusters of purple, yellow and
bright red flowers that sweeten the taste of the air. In the distance
bushes are scattered about in massive clumps huddle underneath lonely trees.

167.name: A Western slope
desc: "   The hillside is surrounded by an ocean of dandilions dancing back and
forth from the gentle winds making the air smell of a fresh
spring day. The warm sunrays dry the soft green grass of the sweet
dew from the night before. In the distance an aloof tree enjoys
the company of friendly bushes by its side finding a cool shade
amid open lands.

168.name: On a Hill-Top with a Stone Marker
desc: "   The top of the hill is flat enough to set up camp. In
the thick soft grass are ashes from a firepit. Someone else has
noticed this good camping spot under the warm sun.
Standing at the top of the hill, right in the centre of
the flattened area is a large stone with some inscriptions
on it.  Looking about, you can see to the distant south, the
walls of Midgard, a grey mass in a sea of green.  To the north
lies a mountain rising out of the plains.
The stone has the image of a warrior engraved on one side.  At
the base you can see some words.  Reading carefully, the words
are nearly worn away, it says
"Here lies the final resting place of
Aruta, Scourge of the Daevae, Slayer
of the Daevish OverLords, shining
example to all races to the glory
and honour of Man"

169.name: An Eastern slope
desc: "   The eastern hillside is approached by a valley of lush
white, yellow, and red flowers, daisies, and giant sunflowers
that stand high above any bush or small person. The colorful
sight runs all the way to the mountains in the northeastern
horizon. In the grass are little red and blue dots that
with a closer look reveal themselves as worker ants carry on
with everyday toils.

268.name: A Southern slope
desc: "   The slightly ascending  grassy knoll leaves the impression of
a naturally constructed ramp due to the gradual elevation. No
roads are present but there are signs of traffic. The tranquilizing
plain pleases the senses with the attar of flowers that sporadically
growing in huge bushes. The singing of birds echoes as they dance
from flower to flower.

589.name: The End of the Road
desc: "   You are at the edge of a great pine forest.  The road
ends just at the start for the forest, but there is a trail
that leads ahead.  To the south you can see a great expanse
of grass, while to the north, your view is blocked by
trees with tall snow-capped mountains framing the skyline.
